Auth Project Documentation
MERN Stack Authentication System

Project Structure Overview

1. Backend (Node.js/Express.js)
Main Components:
- index.js - Main server file
Organized Folders:
- controllers/ - Request handlers
- routes/ - API routes
- models/ - Database schemas
- middleware/ - Custom middleware
- services/ - Business logic
- utils/ - Helper functions
- db/ - Database configuration
- mailtrap/ - Email service integration

2. Frontend (React.js with Vite)
Modern React Setup with:
- Vite as build tool
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- ESLint for code quality
- PostCSS for CSS processing

Steps for Execution

1. Backend Setup
cd backend
npm install
- Ensure MongoDB is installed and running on your system
- Configure environment variables (if any)
- Start the backend server:
npm start

2. Frontend Setup
cd frontend
npm install
- Install dependencies
- Start the development server:
npm run dev

3. Environment Configuration
- Check for .env file in the backend directory
- Configure necessary environment variables:
  - MongoDB connection string
  - JWT secret
  - Port numbers
  - Email service credentials

4. Database Setup
- Ensure MongoDB is running
- The application will create necessary collections automatically

5. Testing the Application
- Backend API endpoints should be accessible (typically on port 5000 or similar)
- Frontend should be running (typically on port 3000 or 5173 for Vite)
- Test the authentication flow:
  - Registration
  - Login
  - Password reset (if implemented)
  - Email verification (if implemented)

